race.comment: FIRE 'N' STONE (6) has made a promising start to her career and should be at peak fitness now. Will land in behind the early speed and be poised to strike when they quicken. SHIRLEY'S TRIBUTE (9) was a smart debut winner here back in July. Forgive run on a bottomless Kembla surface. Her two lead-up trials have only been so-so and she will likely head straight back from the wide alley, but if the pace is genuine she's one to watch for late. BON ELTON (11) plenty of early speed and is drawn to advantage. Will give cheek. YES SIREE (1) has been freshened off two sound efforts to kick off the campaign. Can improve sharply.
